            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>+ In nomine Domini salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/305">Landolfus</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/304">Atenolfus</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/156">Landolfus</persName> divina ordinante
                        providentia Langobardorum gentis <rs key="#Princeps">principes</rs>. Cum
                        principalis excellentia petitionibus dilectorum di (sic) suorum iuste
                        petentibus clementer favet, quapropter noverit <rs key="#Assembly">omnium
                            fidelium nostrorum presentium</rs> scilicet ac futurorum sagacitas
                        quoniam nos Atenolfus misericordia Dei princeps pro mercede et redeptione
                        (sic) anime nostre, quam et per rogum <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/302">Baldoin</persName> venerabilis <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbas</rs> carissimo patri nostro, <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">concessimus atque
                            confirmamus</rs> in ipso sacratissimo <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobi</rs>
                        (sic) <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Slave_labour #Slave #Freeborn"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/84">beati Benedicti</orgName> Christi confesoris
                        (sic) de <rs key="#Mountains">Monte</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Abbots #Monasteries #Rivers #Lakes #Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches" ref="#places/109"
                            >Casino</placeName>, ubi ipse predictus venerabilis abbas preesse
                        videtur, in integrum omnia et in omnivus quantum a
                        singulis principibus antecessoribus nostris ibi offerta atque concessa sunt,
                        per quos omnino sancimus et perpetualiter habendum nostris et futuris
                        temporibus concedimus et confirmamus in eodem cenobio, sicut incipit ab ipso
                            <rs key="#Rivers">Carnello</rs> et ascendente per aquam que dicitur <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Vantra</rs> usque in rivo <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sicco</rs> et ascendente per eodem rivo usque in <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/694">Furcam Sancti Martini</placeName> et inde ascendit per
                        ipse serre et vadit in monte qui dicitur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cisino</rs>, et quomodo vadit im Pesclu qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Corvaru</rs> et quomodo vadit per ipse serre et pervenit ad furcam que
                        vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pubplo</rs> et directum vadit ad lacum qui vocatur <rs key="#Lakes"
                            >Vitecusum</rs> et inde vadit ad <placeName ref="#places/679"
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Aquam Fundatam</placeName> et ascendit inde in ipsum montem qui vocatur
                        de <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sile</rs>, et quomodo vadit in capite de aqua que vocatur <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Rapidu</rs> et quomodo ascendit in montem qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caballu</rs> et vadit directum in montem qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rendenaria maior</rs> et inde per serras montium et pervenit ad <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rendenaria minor</rs>, et quomodo vadit directum per pedes montium qui
                        vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Freselona</rs> et vadit in aqua que vocatur <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >Melarino</rs>, et quomodo vadit per serras montium et pervenit in
                        montem qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/680">Valle Lucis</placeName>, et quomodo vadit per ipsas
                        serras montium et descendit ad <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/692">Petram Scriptam</placeName> et inde ascendit ad serras
                        montis qui dicitur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Ordicosa</rs>, et quomodo vadit per serras montium et pervenit ad
                        pesclora qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/690">Falconari</placeName>, et quomodo salit per duos
                        montes ex quibus unus vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Spinacius</rs> et alter <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Porcacius</rs> et inde ascendit ad cristas montis qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caira</rs> et pervenit ad ipse petre super aqua <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >Vibola</rs> et ascendit ad collem qui vocatur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Gimbiruti</rs>, et quomodo descendit in Quirquintulu et descendit in
                        fosatum (sic) iusta Sanctum Damasum et vadit directum in silice in lo qui
                        dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/687">Arcu de Gizzuli</placeName> et qualiter pergit ad
                        lacum (sic) qui dicitur <rs key="#Lakes">Radeprandi</rs> et qualiter vadit
                        in <placeName ref="#places/686"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Farnitu</placeName> et inde qualiter vadit in rivo qui dicitur <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Marozze</rs> et qualiter descendit in fluvio qui dicitur
                            <rs key="#Rivers">Carnellu</rs> et ascendit per eodem fluvio usque ad
                        aquam qui dicitur <rs key="#Rivers">Cosa</rs> et salit per serram montis qui
                        dicitur <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sancti Donati</rs> et quomodo descendit super ipsi monticelli <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >de Marri</rs> et vadit ad ipsi pascli qui sunt ad pede de ipsum montem
                        de <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Balba</rs>, et quomodo vadit directum per <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/684">Duos Leones</placeName> et inde slit per ipse serre
                        super <placeName ref="#places/685"
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Casale</placeName> et descendit per ipsum montem super ipse <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/682">Ville de Gareliano</placeName> et inde vadit ad Cripta
                        Imperatoris et descendit in fluvio de <rs key="#Rivers">Gareliano</rs> et
                        ascendente per eodem fluvio usque ad priores fines. Simulque et concedimus
                        et in eodem monasterio omnes <rs
                            key="#Freeborn #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >feminas liberas</rs> que sivi servos maritos copulaverunt ipsius
                        monasterii insimul cum eisdem <rs key="#Slave_labour #Slave">servi</rs> sivi
                        copulati cum filiis, filiabus eorum seu et que im predicto sancto cenobio a
                        pontificibus sancte Romane sedis concessa, data aut firmata sunt, quam et
                        illd qui pro sue anime redemptione in eodem sancto cenobio se cum rebus suis
                        offeruerunt vel omnia et in omnibus quantum a singulis principibus
                        antecessoribus nostris ibi offerta atque concessa sunt, ita ut neque a
                        comitibus, gastaldeis seu iudicibus nostris, neque a nulla quampiam homine
                        habeat exinde predictum cenobium aut eius rectores quamcumque molestationem
                        aut contrarietatem, set a presenti et deinceps perpetuis temporibus
                        predictum sacrum cenobium eiusque rectores quamcumque molestationem aut
                        contrarietatem, set a presenti et deinceps perpetuis temporibus predictum
                        sactum cenobium qiusque rectores habeant et possideant iam dicta omnia iure
                        quieto, faciendo exinde quod voluerint in supradicta ratione quemammodum
                        predicti nostri antecessores gloriosi principes insituerunt atque
                        disposuerunt. Porro ut hoc quod iuvemur ab omnibus immobiliter observetur,
                        manu propria scripsimus et anulo nostro iussimus sigillari. Signum domni
                        Atenolfi principis. ATENOLFVS. <persName key="#Notary #Other_clerics"><name
                                ref="Ursus">Ursus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> et <rs key="#Notary">scriba</rs> ex
                        iussione supradicte potestatis scripsi. <date>Data tertio kalendas
                            Februarias in anno quadragesimo tertio principatus domni Landolfi
                            gloriosi principis et decimo anno principatus domni Atenolfi et quarto
                            anno principatus domni Landolfi filii predicti domni Landolfi gloriosi
                            principis, indictione prima. Actu <placeName ref="#places/110"
                                key="#Palatium #Assembly">Beneventi</placeName> in sacro <rs
                                key="#Palatium">Palatio</rs></date>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
